  <scopecontent id="aspace_e231ac7212671f6497dd954fb2b26a9d">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The collection contains 73 original letters and documents of the Lee family, as well as over a dozen items related to other Washington and Lee collections. In addition to Robert E. Lee, other family members represented in the collection include his children, his wife, his parents-in-law, his nephew Fitzhugh, Richard Henry Lee, and Francis Lightfoot Lee. Unrelated correspondants include Margaret Junkin Preston, General P. G. T. Beauregard, and General Joseph E. Johnston.</p>

<p>The sixteen R.E. Lee items cover a date span of 22 years from 1847 through 1869. There are 10 by his wife, Mary Randolph Custis Lee, ranging from the early 1850s in Baltimore, Maryland to shortly before her death in Lexington, Virginia in 1873.</p>    </scopecontent>
